<title>USA: U.S. weekend box office chart -- July 18-20.</title>
<headline>U.S. weekend box office chart -- July 18-20.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Following are the final data for the top 10 movies at the July 18-20 U.S. box office, according to data issued Monday by Exhibitor Relations Co.</p>
<p>    Film			Three-day gross    Cumulative Gross</p>
<p>1. Men in Black		 $19,029,928	 $172,145,793</p>
<p>2. George of the Jungle     $16,540,791	 $ 22,878,989</p>
<p>3. Contact			$16,114,633	 $ 47,408,514</p>
<p>4. Nothing to Lose	    $11,617,767	 $  ----</p>
<p>5. Face/Off		     $ 8,911,744	 $ 86,302,135</p>
<p>6. My Best Friend's Wedding $ 6,522,025	 $ 94,729,094</p>
<p>7. Hercules		     $ 5,192,475	 $ 76,760,217</p>
<p>8. Operation Condor	   $ 4,731,751	 $  ----</p>
<p>9. Out to Sea		   $ 3,170,814	 $ 20,134,766</p>
<p>10 Batman &amp; Robin	     $ 1,780,393	 $102,808,365</p>
<p>NOTE: &quot;Men in Black&quot; is released by Columbia Pictures, a unit of Sony Corp. Sony's TriStar studio released &quot;My Best Friend's Wedding.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;George of the Jungle,&quot; &quot;Nothing to Lose&quot; and &quot;Hercules&quot; are from Walt Disney Co.</p>
<p>Disney's Miramax Films unit released &quot;Operation Condor.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Contact&quot; and &quot;Batman &amp; Robin&quot; are released by Warner Bros, a unit of Time Warner Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;Face/Off&quot; is from Paramount Pictures, a unit of Viacom Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;Out to Sea&quot; is released by 20th Century Fox, a unit of News Corp.</p>
